data.name: Red Borscht
data.quickTastyDescription: A vibrant beet soup that warms the soul, served with a dollop of sour cream and fresh herbs.
detailedCookingInstructions: In a large pot, heat some oil over medium heat and saut√© the chopped onion until translucent.
Add the diced beets, potatoes, and carrots to the pot, stirring occasionally for about 5 minutes.
Pour in the vegetable broth and add shredded cabbage and bay leaves. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and let simmer for about 30 minutes until the vegetables are tender.
Stir in the tomato paste and lemon juice, then season with salt and pepper. Remove bay leaves before serving.
Ladle the soup into bowls and serve hot with a dollop of sour cream and a sprinkle of fresh dill.
data.modifiersForBase: Add sour cream and fresh herbs for a creamy finish
